# Strata Workspace Context

This project is managed by Strata. Read before significant work:

- `.strata/workspace.json` — environment, current goal, technology stack, **structure contract**, active feature, active refresh/retro/crew
- `.strata/memory/summary.md` — project summary
- `.strata/memory/todo.md` — current tasks
- `.strata/memory/architecture.md` — system design, stack, and Structure section
- `.strata/memory/decisions.md` — ADRs and rationale

If `structure.status` is `locked`, respect service roots and expected paths (see `18-structure-contract.mdc` / `strata-structure-contract.mdc`).

After significant work, update relevant memory files.

## Branch Safety

Never checkout or edit on protected trunk branches directly. Strata forks new work branches from selected bases. Respect `trunkLocked` and safety warnings.

## Active Missions

If `.strata/refresh/current.md` exists or `strata-active-refresh.mdc` is present, follow the RCA Refresh protocol until archived. Phase 0 prohibits mutations.

If `.strata/retro/current.md` exists or `strata-active-retro.mdc` is present, follow the Retro protocol until archived. Edit rules/memory only — not product code.

If `.strata/crew/current.md` exists or `strata-active-crew.mdc` is present, follow the Multi-Agent Crew protocol (`crew-protocol.mdc`): Planner fills `contract.md`, specialists use separate Agents Window sessions (prefer worktrees), then Integrator merges.

At session end, user may invoke Retro to evolve doctrine.
